title: Prostitutka (1927)
description:
Plot: Recorded from a Channel 4 broadcast many many years ago. Excellent quality for a VHS to DVD transfer. Very good newly commissioned score for the film too. Running Time: 77mins

The director is the Russian Oleg Froelich - at least that's the way Jay Leyda spells his name in his Russian cinema history "Kino" where this film is briefly mentioned.  I suppose the correct spelling is Frelikh as in the imdb entry for the film link

According to Leyda, it was the first film of the studio Byelgoskino.  According to imdb, it was their only film!  (And the only one directed by Frelikh.) Excellent use of the close-up too!
